revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
<!-- Add categories where indicated at the bottom of this page and interwikis at Wikidata -->
{{lua|Module:Portal bar}}

== Purpose ==
Easy-to-use template for creating icon tables of related portals for portal pages. Friendly to wide and narrow screens alike, including mobile, and does not require hardcoding icons, etc.

== Usage ==
Similar to the [[Template:Portal]] inline box; simply provide a list of related portals to show, such as:

<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" style="overflow:auto;">
{{Related portals|Agriculture and Agronomy|Medicine|Schools|Spain}}
</syntaxhighlight>

{{Related portals|Agriculture and Agronomy|Medicine|Schools|Spain}}

== Wide and narrow screens ==
This system uses CSS flexbox to fit within the browser's window, which allows it to scale to wide screens and narrow ones, like on mobile:

<div style="border:2px solid gray; width: 320px">
{{Related portals|Agriculture and Agronomy|Medicine|Schools|Spain}}
</div>

== Image ==
The portal image name is found using [[Module:Portal]]. Please see [[Module:Portal#Image]] for instructions on how to add, update, or remove an image.

== See also ==
* {{tl|Portal}}
* {{tl|Portal bar}}
{{portal template list}}

